    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "FIRST FLIGHT\n*\nTIRLINES\nLOCKHEED\nPROP-JET ELECTRA\nwith GM JET POWER\nAllison 501 Prop-Jet Engines and\nAeroproducts 606 Turbo-Propellers\nAPP26\n8.30 AM\n19:59\nU:S. AIR\nAIRPIZE:\nSTATEHOOD • 1959\nAir Mail\nCol. J. H. Lackey, Jr.\nARGIN - IB TUSLOG\nRM4B137, Pentagon\nWashington 25, D3 C..\nSan yor\n37 TR 04",
      "SOMES TIE\nSO THO\n• 4 MAY 1959\n6561\nКоломня\n202,149,2014a",
      "This first flight cachet commemorates the first flight of the four-engine\nLockheed Electra luxuryliner on routes of National Airlines. This is another\nin a series of cachets being made available as major world airlines phase into\ncommercial service the 450-mph transports, with the General Motors Jet Power\nteam of Allison Model 501-D13 Prop-jet engines and Aeroproducts 606 Turbo-\npropellers.\nVice-President of General Motors\nGeneral Manager of Allison Division",
      "2012.149.20146"
    ],
